INSERT INTO `news` VALUES (35,1,'2018-04-02','<p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Dear Investors,</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Below is our report for the month of February, in which we focus on discussing the challenges we face with product development and customer adoption, accelerating product development, and the timing for revenue in 2018. We describe the challenges as well as our current thinking about how to gain more traction and move faster. Any feedback, advice, or questions are appreciated.</p><h1 style=\"margin: 30px 0px 10px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(65, 202, 192); border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(204, 241, 236); font-size: 20px !important;\">Highlights</h1><h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;\">Needs / Asks:</h2><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 0px; margin-left: 20px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">We are continuing to seek additional members for our governance and advisory boards. If you have any suggestions of people in your network who you think may have experience either on the technical or agricultural side, please let us know.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">If you know anyone that has prior work experience working with the top retailers (Costco, Whole Foods, Kroger, Walmart), please contact us. We want to better understand our customer’s customers. We may not yet be ready for an introduction, but we would like to identify potential contacts early.</p></li></ul><h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;\">KPIs</h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">As our company is moving towards more operational and robust service products, we are considering updating our KPI’s to reflect this change. New metrics we have discussed include: Total number of customers, acres under management, margin dollars generated, and operational service products.</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 0px; margin-left: 20px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Number of customers in the list of Top 25 Growers/Processors in the Western U.S.:</span>&nbsp;1</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Number of customers/partners in the list of Top 25 Growers/Processors in Europe:</span>&nbsp;1</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Acres of target crops analyzed to date:</span>&nbsp;23,100</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Specialty Crop Types:</span>&nbsp;4</p></li></ul><h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;\">Successes</h2><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 0px; margin-left: 20px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">Collected imagery over Bonipak fields in Santa Maria, both high resolution, algorithm training data and lower resolution data for broader area coverage. The latter data are of a resolution consistent with other data we have collected from Aeroptic and Sanborn.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">Evaluated potential operational imagery collection partners such as AUV and GeoWing for longer-term relationships.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">Agreed to a pricing model with Bonipak Board for long-term strategic partnership, as well as potential margin generating product development and research.</p></li></ul><h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;\">Challenges</h2><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 0px; margin-left: 20px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">Customer acquisition has been slow. We have not been able to progress the relationships with T&amp;A, Church, and Taylor Farms. This is related to a combination of factors: value did not meet their original expectations, poor timing as they are now transitioning back from Yuma, that we are potentially not speaking with the right people, and that we do not yet have solutions that demonstrate undeniable value. We will continue to work on these relationships, as well as seek to refine our sales process to shorten the cycle time as we continue to advance our technical solutions.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">Our timeline for substantial, operational revenue generation has increased, as we are focused on moving faster with technology development to get ahead of our competition with a stronger product-market fit. This does not mean that we will be ceasing our sales efforts, simply that we are focused on technology development as the main priority in the near term.</p></li></ul><h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;\">Insights</h2><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 0px; margin-left: 20px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">As we continue to evaluate imaging sensors, one of the key metrics we have identified is total data throughput, both in terms of the speed at which the sensor can capture data and also in terms of how quickly it can write the data to storage.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">Based on the movements of Tanimura and Antle, Church Brothers, Taylor Farms and Bowles, we have decided to put our full focus into the Bonipak and G’s partnerships. We believe that this will give us enough momentum, customer insight, and competitive advantage to re-engage with these customers at the right levels with more value.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">The partnership with Bonipak has been invaluable in terms of the ability to access fields for a longitudinal study, as well as being able to tune the product directly to the customer’s needs. Bonipak has also opened their organization to our team so that we can learn about the multiple divisions within their company that can receive a positive ROI from our technology. This will be integral for demonstrating value to other customers in the industry. They have also introduced us to the number 2 grower in Europe.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">As we continue to evaluate aerial vendors, we have learned that those that provide and manufacture the hardware, such as Altavian, tend not to be well suited to provide consistent service operations for our customers. Typically, they lack the photogrammetric, sensor and image quality expertise necessary for our processes. We have identified two other groups, AUV and GeoWing, with this type of expertise moving forward.</p></li></ul><h1 style=\"margin: 30px 0px 10px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(65, 202, 192); border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(204, 241, 236); font-size: 20px !important;\">In Depth</h1><h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;\">Current Customers</h2><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 0px; margin-left: 20px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Number of Customers:</span>&nbsp;2</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Current Customers:</span>&nbsp;Bonipak/Betteravia Farms, G’s</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Bonipak/Betteravia Farms:</span>&nbsp;The relationship with Bonipak is progressing well, and we are in the final stages of a partnership agreement where they would be supporting our product development and research. While this will not be our operational model, we believe that our relationship with Bonipak is critical at this stage in the business. Not only will they continue to point us towards customer value, but they will also help us generate revenue for development. We have met with all of their partners, Board, and senior leadership, and have received consensus to move forward with our pricing model.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">G’s:</span>&nbsp;One of the top five growers in Europe who has been working on some of their own remote sensing software. Much like the other grower/processors, they go from seed to shelf. We are in the process of negotiating a partnership agreement with them to co-develop software.</p></li></ul><h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;\">Customer Pipeline</h2><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 0px; margin-left: 20px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Tanimura &amp; Antle:</span>&nbsp;We have still not had substantial contact with senior-level executives at T&amp;A. We will continue to reach out during their transition back from Yuma.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Church Brothers:</span>&nbsp;We are continuing to work with Church, however, progress towards an operational sale has been slow. While they are interested in what we are doing, we are not sure that there is enough value to them at the current price point that we are able to deliver. To that effect, we are evaluating superior sensors and platforms that may enable us to roll out the product at a price that delivers them a measurable and significant ROI.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">JV Smith</span>: Because we were never able to provide enough value for JV Smith, we did not invoice the company, and are therefore putting them back into the customer pipeline. It seems that they were primarily interested in looking at early stand numbers to validate their automatic thinning technology. They have acknowledged that knowing head size variability at harvest would be valuable, however, we have not been able demonstrate to get them to quantify this capability or to get them to quantify this value.value We will continue to keep contact with them, however, as they represent a proof case of a major Grower customer.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Bowles Farming Company</span>: Bowles remains interested in doing a project, albeit at a much smaller scale. They have stated that their main priorities are bringing their other operation systems, such as accounting, payroll, and personnel tracking, up to speed before looking towards the next stage technologies. We will be working on establishing a small pilot project with them to collect data this season, to develop a product for them to be used for next season.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Customer Pipeline:</span>&nbsp;D’Arrigo Brothers, Taylor Farms, Grower’s Express, Bowles Farming Company, Ocean Mist, Nunes Vegetables, Duda Farm Fresh Foods, Earthbound Farms, Braga Farms, Coastline Family Farms.</p></li></ul><h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;\">Product</h2><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 0px; margin-left: 20px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">We have migrated our entire backend to a larger Microsoft Azure account and are now working on getting the system ready for remote operations. Importantly this will decrease our turnaround time for our customers, and in some cases, increase the ROI for our products.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">We have used the various imagery sets we have collected to improve the accuracy of our “dirt mask”, which differentiates plants from dirt and thereby increases the accuracy of plant detection. This capability has the potential of being a new product offering – to tell customers actual planted acres of crop versus planned acres. Church Brothers has expressed interest in this capability specifically.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">The engineering team has developed some simple imagery Q/C software tools that will allow us to evaluate the quality of the imagery in the field. This will allow us to more quickly iterate on the field testing of sensors, drones, and imagery resolutions while ensuring the quality necessary for our analytics.</p></li></ul><h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;\">Team</h2><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 0px; margin-left: 20px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Current Team:</span>&nbsp;Jeff Orrey, Bernie Johnston, Chris Ewing, Charles McGregor, Andrew Catellier, Matthew Kotalik, Jen Anderson, Michael Chebatoris, with Andrew McGregor now devoting more of his time in the interim as Chairman and Executive Director</li></ul><h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;\">Partnerships</h2><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 0px; margin-left: 20px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">GeoWing:</span>&nbsp;We have utilized GeoWing twice now to help us collect high-resolution imagery over Bonipak’s fields, as well as to help us collect ground control points (GCPs) that increase the geolocation accuracy of the imagery and therefore our ability to locate plants in the field. They have been effective both times, collecting some of the best quality imagery we have had access to. We are still in the process of vetting them as a consistent operational partner, versus for research specific purposes.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">AUV:</span>&nbsp;AUV also collected high-resolution imagery, however, they were using a manned, fixed-wing aircraft over Bonipak’s fields. We jumped on this opportunity because they were already in Los Angeles, flying a project over the city, and we were able to have them fly the fields in Santa Maria for a significantly reduced rate since they did not have to mobilize a crew. This speaks to the value of having local pilots in each location that we have a primary customer.</p></li></ul><h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;\">Market</h2><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 0px; margin-left: 20px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">FarmShots, a company that analyzes drone and satellite imagery, was acquired by Syngenta. Their company, to the best of our knowledge, is primarily focused on corn and soy. They are specifically providing technology to reduce scouting efforts through NDVI / Health heat maps, as well as to reduce fertilizer application. They had only raised $1.1m in funding up to the point of acquisition, speaking to a potential for early acquisition if you are able to move the farmers from classic paper records and excel spreadsheets to cloud databases and web dashboards. Many of the larger companies are looking for companies that have that sort of digital relationship with the more historic growers.</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">Walmart filed for patents related to pest detection, pest spraying, and crop pollination using drones. This is compelling in the sense they are moving to take more control of their supply side to compete with Amazon and an increasingly competitive landscape of retailers. There is a potential for a technology like ours to either augment their current filings or potentially be able to provide similar value to one of their competitors.</p></li></ul><h2 style=\"font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;\">Competitors</h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">We have done a comprehensive reevaluation of the investment activity and competitive landscape, as well as significantly more research into the currently identified competitors. This has left us with a greater understanding of the path forward, confidence there are strong exit opportunities, as well as reinforced that we must move even faster to capture market share in our target crops. Each of the competitors identified below has the potential to become a direct competitor. We have a multi-layered competitive research process that will help us keep in front of their movements in the market. If there is enough interest from our investors, we will set up a meeting/conference call to talk about the process and the competitors.</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 0px; margin-left: 20px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Currently Identified Proximate Competitors:</span>&nbsp;PrecisionHawk, Agremo, Intelinair, RaptorMaps, Prospera, Agribotix, Gamaya, Taranis, SlantRange, Ceres Imaging, FluroSat, Mavrx, HummingBird Technologies, Resson, FarmShots, Agridata.ai</li></ul><h1 style=\"margin: 30px 0px 10px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(65, 202, 192); border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(204, 241, 236); font-size: 20px !important;\">Financials</h1><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Monthly financial tracking graphs:</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><img src=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-1vR7Yna63rUwWzvYablmZ_10NEd8rwrxtyuNTIKStZvYy4oWSG4-E0Xz0mxgnHh2sUAFPPeI4wPm56o-/pubchart?oid=1600149935&amp;format=image\" alt=\"Cash Balance + AR\" style=\"border: 0px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-1vR7Yna63rUwWzvYablmZ_10NEd8rwrxtyuNTIKStZvYy4oWSG4-E0Xz0mxgnHh2sUAFPPeI4wPm56o-/pubchart?oid=1478465657&amp;format=image\" alt=\"Burn Rate\" style=\"border: 0px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-1vR7Yna63rUwWzvYablmZ_10NEd8rwrxtyuNTIKStZvYy4oWSG4-E0Xz0mxgnHh2sUAFPPeI4wPm56o-/pubchart?oid=1626690490&amp;format=image\" alt=\"Head Count\" style=\"border: 0px;\"></p><h1 style=\"margin: 30px 0px 10px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(65, 202, 192); border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(204, 241, 236); font-size: 20px !important;\">Short Term Goals</h1><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 0px; margin-left: 20px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">Complete strategic partnership negotiations with Bonipak/Betteravia</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">Pursue Church Brothers as a 2018 customer</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">Analyze multiple sensors and drone platforms for longitudinal study in Santa Maria</p></li><li style=\"list-style-position: outside;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\">Develop advanced analytics in conjunction with Bonipak and G’s</p></li></ul><h1 style=\"margin: 30px 0px 10px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(65, 202, 192); border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(204, 241, 236); font-size: 20px !important;\">Exit Strategy</h1><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The filings of Walmart have not introduced a new potential exit; however, they have reinforced that the retailers will begin looking more thoroughly at technologies that create efficiencies throughout their supply chain. This includes insights into yields, pests, diseases, and total market supply. We continue to see five main exit scenarios: Grower/Packer/Shipper or Industry Collective, Industrial Agriculture, Agriculture Logistics/Analytics, Large Retail, and PE rollup.</p><hr style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border-top-color: rgb(238, 238, 238); color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(121, 121, 121); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Sincerely, The GeoVisual Team</p>'),(37,12,'2018-05-10','<h1 class=\"x_update-title\" style=\"color: rgb(74, 75, 77); font-family: Whitney, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, serif, EmojiFont; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold;\">CaliberMind Q1 Investor Update + Financials&nbsp;</h1><div class=\"x_update-html-section\" style=\"color: rgb(74, 75, 77); font-family: Whitney, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, serif, EmojiFont;\"><h2 style=\"font-size: 22px; margin: 30px 0px 8px;\">Summary&nbsp;</h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px;\">Spring is here and it\'s time for our quarterly update. In Q1 we had to take a step back with product and sales in 